00},{"title":"Author/Toshiya Teraishi","target":"Author/Toshiya Teraishi","line":101},{"title":"Author/Toshiya Teraishi","target":"Author/Toshiya Teraishi","line":102},{"title":"Author/Satoko Obu","target":"Author/Satoko Obu","line":103},{"title":"Author/Satoko Obu","target":"Author/Satoko Obu","line":104},{"title":"Author/Hayato Ozawa","target":"Author/Hayato Ozawa","line":105},{"title":"Author/Hayato Ozawa","target":"Author/Hayato Ozawa","line":106},{"title":"Author/Hiroshi Kunugi","target":"Author/Hiroshi Kunugi","line":107},{"title":"Author/Hiroshi Kunugi","target":"Author/Hiroshi Kunugi","line":108},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/ota_effect_2014/ota_effect_2014.pdf","line":110}],"metadata":{"id":"ota_effect_2014","type":"article-journal","title":"Effect of L-theanine on sensorimotor gating in healthy human subjects.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2014]]},"DOI":"10.1111/pcn.12134","container-title":"Psychiatry and Clinical Neurosciences","abstract":"Aim l-Theanine (N-ethyl-l-glutamine) is an amino acid uniquely found in green tea. Growing evidence has suggested the possible effects of l-theanine on cognition. Previously, we found that l-theanine attenuates MK-801-induced deficit in prepulse inhibition (PPI) in mice. In this study, we examined the effect of l-theanine in increasing the PPI in healthy humans. Methods The subjects were 14 healthy adults who underwent PPI testing as a measure of sensorimotor gating 90min after an oral intake of l-theanine (0, 200, 400, or 600mg). PPI tests were done by examiners who were blind to the dose. Results The administration of 200mg of l-theanine and that of 400mg, but not 600mg, significantly increased the % PPI compared to the baseline (0mg). There was no significant relation between the dose of l-theanine and the startle magnitude or the habituation of startle response. The plasma concentrations of l-theanine correlated with the dose of l-theanine. Conclusion The observed effect with 200–400mg of l-theanine on PPI suggested that l-theanine at a particular dose range increases sensorimotor gating in humans.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Ota","given":"Miho","literal":""},{"family":"Ota","given":"Miho","literal":""},{"family":"Wakabayashi","given":"Chisato","literal":""},{"family":"Wakabayashi","given":"Chisato","literal":""},{"family":"Matsuo","given":"Junko","literal":""},{"family":"Matsuo","given":"Junko","literal":""},{"family":"Kinoshita","given":"Yukiko","literal":""},{"family":"Kinoshita","given":"Yukiko","literal":""},{"family":"Hori","given":"Hiroaki","literal":""},{"family":"Hori","given":"Hiroaki","literal":""},{"family":"Hattori","given":"Kotaro","literal":""},{"family":"Hattori","given":"Kotaro","literal":""},{"family":"Sasayama","given":"Daimei","literal":""},{"family":"Sasayama","given":"Daimei","literal":""},{"family":"Teraishi","given":"Toshiya","literal":""},{"family":"Teraishi","given":"Toshiya","literal":""},{"family":"Obu","given":"Satoko","literal":""},{"family":"Obu","given":"Satoko","literal":""},{"family":"Ozawa","given":"Hayato","literal":""},{"family":"Ozawa","given":"Hayato","literal":""},{"family":"Kunugi","given":"Hiroshi","literal":""},{"family":"Kunugi","given":"Hiroshi","literal":""}],"citation-key":"ota_effect_2014","year":"2014","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Effect of L-theanine on sensorimotor gating in healthy human subjects."],"author-links":["[[Author/Miho Ota]]","[[Author/Miho Ota]]","[[Author/Chisato Wakabayashi]]","[[Author/Chisato Wakabayashi]]","[[Author/Junko Matsuo]]","[[Author/Junko Matsuo]]","[[Author/Yukiko Kinoshita]]","[[Author/Yukiko Kinoshita]]","[[Author/Hiroaki Hori]]","[[Author/Hiroaki Hori]]","[[Author/Kotaro Hattori]]","[[Author/Kotaro Hattori]]","[[Author/Daimei Sasayama]]","[[Author/Daimei Sasayama]]","[[Author/Toshiya Teraishi]]","[[Author/Toshiya Teraishi]]","[[Author/Satoko Obu]]","[[Author/Satoko Obu]]","[[Author/Hayato Ozawa]]","[[Author/Hayato Ozawa]]","[[Author/Hirosh